    "content": "nullSalesforce B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Salesforce B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\n Commerce Basics\n Get Started with Salesforce Commerce\n Import and Export Commerce Data\n Access to Commerce Stores\n Products and Pricing\n Configure Checkout for a Commerce Store\n Store Search\n Search Engine Optimization (SEO) for Commerce\n Commerce Einstein\n Einstein and Data Usage in Commerce Cloud\n Data Cloud for Commerce\n Store Management\n Goals and Recommendations\n Shopper Copilot for Commerce Stores\n Get Help with Store Issues with the Troubleshooting Assistant\n Using Salesforce CMS for Product Media\n Assign a CMS Public Channel to a Commerce Store\n Commerce Workspaces\n Manage Pricing in the Pricing Workspace\n Manage Products in the Product Workspace\n Search the Product Workspace\n Manage Promotions with the Promotion Workspace\n Manage Buyers and Shoppers in the Customer Workspace\n Migrate Your Store Configuration\n Commerce Analytics\n Create Custom Reports with Search and Category Data for B2B Stores\n Manage Integrations for Your Store\n Set Up Inventory for Commerce Stores\n Replace a Default Commerce Process with an Apex Class\n Create Email Order Confirmation Notifications\n Configure What Shoppers or Buyers See When a Store Isn’t Available\n Commerce Promotions\n Sell Globally\n Website Design for Commerce Stores\n Publication and Activation\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nB2B COMMERCE AND D2C COMMERCE\nManage Promotions with the Promotion Workspace\n\nThe Promotion Workspace consolidates all your promotions in one place. You can use filters to focus on a particular store, buyer group, or promotion field. Quickly see which promotions are active, and change the status of multiple promotions at the same time. Create promotions or edit existing ones.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: Lightning Experience\nAvailable in: Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions\nAvailable in: B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\nIMPORTANT As of Summer ’24, there’s a refreshed Commerce app, which we encourage you to use. The navigation steps in this Help documentation reflect the new app. If you’re still using the previous app, now called the Commerce Storefront Console, see B2B and D2C Commerce Using the Commerce Storefront Console. For instructions on switching to the refreshed app, see Enable the Refreshed Commerce App.\nIn the navigation sidebar, select a store from the Store dropdown.\nClick Promotions.\nChoose which information to display by adding or removing columns.\nClick the gear icon, and select Select Columns to Display.\nUse the arrows to move items between Available Columns and Selected Columns.\nClick Save.\nTo filter the list:\nClick the filter icon, and select Add Filter.\nSelect Promotions Assigned To or Promotion Field.\nSelect the operator and value.\nClick Save.\nTo apply the filter to your list of promotions, click Apply.\nTo create a promotions list, click the gear icon, select New, name the list, and save it\nTo activate or deactivate one or more promotions:\nSelect the promotions.\nClick an action button at the top of the screen. If the action that you’re looking for isn’t displayed on the screen, click the dropdown arrow next to the action buttons.\nChoose whether to activate or deactivate the promotion.\nNOTE When a customer adds products to the cart, Salesforce evaluates the first 50 active manual promotions and the first 50 active automation promotions for the customer’s account to determine if they apply. To improve performance, we recommend activating and prioritizing only the promotions that you need.\nTo edit a field in a promotion or promotion list, hover your cursor over it, and click the pencil icon.\nTo update multiple fields with the same value, select the items to be edited, click the pencil icon, and then select the option to update the selected items.\nTo add a promotion to the workspace, click New from the action buttons at the top of the screen, and enter the promotion details.\nSEE ALSO\nCommerce Promotions\nCommerce Workspaces\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
